If you prefer to make potato or meat tacos then cook then whichever way you prefer. The same goes for chicken preparation--any which way is good. Remove the skin from the chicken and cut it into pieces. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fd/490772-1-bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-490772-1-bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fd/490772-1-bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-490772-1-bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Put the water to boil in pot big enough to fit the chicken. Put the following ingredients into the pot: 2 spoons of salt, 1/2 an onion cut into chunks, 3 garlic cloves, 1 teaspoon of oregano, the chicken pieces. Leave the chicken in for about 20 minutes. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/84/490772-1-bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-490772-1-bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/84/490772-1-bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-490772-1-bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Take the chicken out of the pot and make sure it is cooked. If it is not put it back in for a few more minutes. Otherwise let the chicken cool. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/490772-1-bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-490772-1-bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/490772-1-bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-490772-1-bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Creative Commons</a>
</p></div>"}

Start shredding the pieces of chicken. These strips will go in the taco so make sure the pieces are the right size. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/490772-1-bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-490772-1-bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/490772-1-bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-490772-1-bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
